trend_summary: The landscape stays mainly agricultural. Built-up growth is modest, adding houses around the main crossroads and along the east-west road, but no sizable town forms. Northern hill forest is first reduced, then partially replanted. Fields become larger and more regular, reflecting farm consolidation, and a minor new road link appears.

Ribbon housing added sporadically on secondary roads, increasing scattered dwellings.
Northern hillside forest shows mid-period clearance followed by later regrowth.
Hedgerow removal and field amalgamation create larger, more uniform parcels.
Construction or widening of a bypass/new connector south of the main settlement.
